notes: The LLM reported 'safe' with 0 findings, but the ground truth identifies a real logic error in getSwapFee. The vulnerability exists: getSwapFee has a hardcoded ceiling of 100_000 ppm (10%) that silently discards higher fees from DynamicSwapFeeModule (which allows up to 50%), causing governance to believe protective high fees are active when users only pay the tiny tick-spacing default. This is a valid TARGET vulnerability that was missed entirely.
